00:17:30.955 --> 00:17:35.083
energy are categories that human beings have created,

462
00:17:35.083 --> 00:17:36.139
never discovered.

463
00:17:36.139 --> 00:17:37.301
We've defined them.

464
00:17:37.301 --> 00:17:39.488
In a similar fashion, we didn't discover religion.

465
00:17:39.488 --> 00:17:41.440
We human beings, we in the West,

466
00:17:41.440 --> 00:17:44.149
have defined religion according to our constructs,

467
00:17:44.149 --> 00:17:45.749
our framework,

468
00:17:45.749 --> 00:17:47.722
and it's really overwhelmingly defined by the

469
00:17:47.722 --> 00:17:50.506
salient characteristics of the Abrahamic religions.

470
00:17:50.506 --> 00:17:53.183
They start out, I think without exception, really,

471
00:17:53.183 --> 00:17:56.297
with very deep ontological or metaphysical claims

472
00:17:56.297 --> 00:18:00.595
that we cannot readily test by experience.

473
00:18:00.595 --> 00:18:02.366
In the beginning, God created.

474
00:18:02.366 --> 00:18:04.819
In the beginning was the word, the word was made flesh.

475
00:18:04.819 --> 00:18:09.437
There is but one God, and Muhammed is his prophet.

476
00:18:09.437 --> 00:18:12.744
Well, those may be true claims,

477
00:18:12.744 --> 00:18:15.058
but how on earth do we know?

478
00:18:15.058 --> 00:18:16.136
And how on earth do we ever put that

479
00:18:16.136 --> 00:18:18.151
to the test of experience, right?

480
00:18:18.151 --> 00:18:21.543
Buddhism radically doesn't start out that way,

481
00:18:21.543 --> 00:18:24.018
and so, really, what it is worthwhile asking

482
00:18:24.018 --> 00:18:29.018
is it appropriate, is it revealing or more obscuring,

483
00:18:29.289 --> 00:18:32.317
to simply dump Buddhism into the category of religion

484
00:18:32.317 --> 00:18:33.651
that's already been defined

485
00:18:33.651 --> 00:18:36.051
according to three Western religions.

486
00:18:36.051 --> 00:18:37.736
Buddhism doesn't start there.

487
00:18:37.736 --> 00:18:40.339
And I must say it was not because of the deepest claims,

488
00:18:40.339 --> 00:18:43.506
the ultimate nature of awareness or these kind of claims,

489
00:18:43.506 --> 00:18:47.592
that really held me, gripped me, and then inspired me

490
00:18:47.592 --> 00:18:50.514
to want to go deeper and deeper and deeper.

491
00:18:50.514 --> 00:18:52.893
Rather, Buddhism starts with experience.

492
00:18:52.893 --> 00:18:54.983
Experience right now, here and now,

493
00:18:54.983 --> 00:18:57.116
not what happened long ago in the universe,

494
00:18:57.116 --> 00:19:00.391
or what's the ultimate dimension of consciousness,

495
00:19:00.391 --> 00:19:04.103
which of course we can't easily fathom either.

496
00:19:04.103 --> 00:19:06.097
It starts out with here, there's a reality of

497
00:19:06.097 --> 00:19:07.622
let's call it dissatisfaction.

498
00:19:07.622 --> 00:19:09.148
There's that word dukkha.

499
00:19:09.148 --> 00:19:12.518
The dissatisfaction goes from boredom, malaise...

500
00:19:12.518 --> 00:19:13.809
<v Interviewer>The opposite of sukha.</v>

501
00:19:13.809 --> 00:19:14.992
<v ->It's the opposite of sukha,</v>

502
00:19:14.992 --> 00:19:16.774
but it covers a whole bandwidth here.

503
00:19:16.774 --> 00:19:20.411
If you have a little itch on your kneecap.

504
00:19:20.411 --> 00:19:22.181
Oh, that itches, I don't like that.

505
00:19:22.181 --> 00:19:23.419
That would be dukkha.

506
00:19:23.419 --> 00:19:24.805
I don't like it.

507
00:19:24.805 --> 00:19:26.245
That's pretty trivial.

508
00:19:26.245 --> 00:19:29.498
All the way to anguish, to physical torment,

509
00:19:29.498 --> 00:19:31.589
white hot pain.

510
00:19:31.589 --> 00:19:33.189
The whole spectrum is dukkha.

511
00:19:33.189 --> 00:19:35.631
But likewise then we have this corollary term,

512
00:19:35.631 --> 00:19:37.188
the antonym, and that is sukha,

513
00:19:37.188 --> 00:19:38.959
and that's everything from,

514
00:19:38.959 --> 00:19:43.959
"I like that feeling on my cheek," you know, kinda,

515
00:19:44.121 --> 00:19:48.750
to bliss, to ecstasy, to inconceivable sense of well being.

516
00:19:48.750 --> 00:19:51.716
But then this is where Buddhism...

517
00:19:51.716 --> 00:19:53.816
