Well, there's this kind of entry level,

773
00:28:48.545 --> 00:28:51.820
which is an absolutely indispensable foundation,

774
00:28:51.820 --> 00:28:53.078
living ethically.

775
00:28:53.078 --> 00:28:54.582
So whatever your preferences are and so forth,

776
00:28:54.582 --> 00:28:57.889
more subtle issues, at least do no harm.

777
00:28:57.889 --> 00:28:59.659
At least that, you know.

778
00:28:59.659 --> 00:29:01.345
And then if you can spiritual on top of that,

779
00:29:01.345 --> 00:29:02.785
if you want to meditate, or you want to go

780
00:29:02.785 --> 00:29:04.982
into subtler dimensions, that's all very well,

781
00:29:04.982 --> 00:29:08.128
but in the mean time at least don't do any harm here.

782
00:29:08.128 --> 00:29:12.213
And then we move into this area of self centered desires.

783
00:29:12.213 --> 00:29:14.165
Self centered desires, and then as soon as I have

784
00:29:14.165 --> 00:29:16.565
a self centered desire and sometime gets in the way,

785
00:29:16.565 --> 00:29:19.146
then I have a self centered anger,

786
00:29:19.146 --> 00:29:22.090
or I have a self centered desire that doesn't happen,

787
00:29:22.090 --> 00:29:23.711
and then somebody dishes that up,

788
00:29:23.711 --> 00:29:25.588
or maybe just reality dishes it up,

789
00:29:25.588 --> 00:29:27.294
I get angry at reality?

790
00:29:27.294 --> 00:29:28.650
Which is not a very good idea.

791
00:29:28.650 --> 00:29:32.468
And so there, once again, now we're working

792
00:29:32.468 --> 00:29:35.838
not so much on behaviour, but now how the mind functions.

793
00:29:35.838 --> 00:29:38.420
This is what I was alluding to earlier today

794
00:29:38.420 --> 00:29:40.553
when I spoke of equality of well being,

795
00:29:40.553 --> 00:29:43.849
foundationally, that arises from leading

796
00:29:43.849 --> 00:29:45.715
an ethical way of life,

797
00:29:45.715 --> 00:29:48.094
so you can die without remorse.

798
00:29:48.094 --> 00:29:49.982
You have a sense of blamelessness that

799
00:29:49.982 --> 00:29:52.136
I didn't do much damage, and I really tried to

800
00:29:52.136 --> 00:29:53.864
do some good where I could.

801
00:29:53.864 --> 00:29:54.984
Good foundation.

802
00:29:54.984 --> 00:29:57.704
But then there's a whole other level of well being.

803
00:29:57.704 --> 00:29:59.122
And all of this, I must say, gradually

804
00:29:59.122 --> 00:30:03.111
dawned on me during these early years that I was training,

805
00:30:03.111 --> 00:30:05.319
very intensively, from the early '70s,

806
00:30:05.319 --> 00:30:06.802
in Dharamsala.

807
00:30:06.802 --> 00:30:09.116
But then there's another whole dimension of well being

808
00:30:09.116 --> 00:30:13.351
that comes not simply how we conduct ourselves,

809
00:30:13.351 --> 00:30:16.540
by way of speech and by physical behaviour,

810
00:30:16.540 --> 00:30:19.324
but now the actual cultivation of the mind,

811
00:30:19.324 --> 00:30:22.993
and recognizing I can sit in a room all by myself

812
00:30:22.993 --> 00:30:25.478
and make myself utterly miserable.

813
00:30:25.478 --> 00:30:27.505
I can also... There are yogis,

814
00:30:27.505 --> 00:30:29.990
there are others, who can sit all by themselves in a room

815
00:30:29.990 --> 00:30:31.792
and be utterly content,

816
00:30:31.792 --> 00:30:33.275
and actually experience bliss.

817
00:30:33.275 --> 00:30:35.493
And not only in isolation, as if they just

818
00:30:35.493 --> 00:30:37.690
have a high dopamine level or something like that,

819
00:30:37.690 --> 00:30:39.898
but a profound sense of connectedness.

820
00:30:39.898 --> 00:30:42.821
The Dalai Lama was asked once whether he ever feels lonely.

821
00:30:42.821 --> 00:30:45.381
Here he is, you know, he's had a very unusual life.

822
00:30:45.381 --> 00:30:47.034
He said, "No, I never feel lonely.

823
00:30:47.034 --> 00:30:49.327
"Whether I am with others or whether I'm in solitude,

824
00:30:49.327 --> 00:30:51.844
"I always feel a sense of connectedness."

825
00:30:51.844 --> 00:30:54.042
The sense of empathy, the sense of caring

826
00:30:54.042 --> 00:30:56.068
for the greater world,

827
00:30:56.068 --> 00:30:57.833
even if you're spending some time in solitude.

828
00:30:57.833 --> 00:31:00.585
So there's a whole arena there, a whole domain

829
00:31:00.585 --> 00:31:04.179
of meditative practice that we call samadhi,

830
00:31:04.179 --> 00:31:06.355
or we can call, more broadly, meditation.

831
00:31:06.355 --> 00:31:08.755
It's not something esoteric or occultish

832
00:31:08.755 --> 00:31:10.211
or paranormal or weird.

833
00:31:10.211 --> 00:31:14.098
The cultivation of the mind is specifically

834
00:31:14.098 --> 00:31:17.597
recognizing those tendencies in the mind, those impulses,

835
00:31:17.597 --> 00:31:20.989
that are destructive to our own and others' well being,

836
00:31:20.989 --> 00:31:23.079
and those tendencies that are conducive

837
00:31:23.079 --> 00:31:25.351
to our own and others' well being,

838
00:31:25.351 --> 00:31:27.591
and then, just like a gardener coming into a field,

839
00:31:27.591 --> 00:31:29.169
a field of one's own mind,

840
00:31:29.169 --> 00:31:32.988
then seeing how can I gradually weed out,

841
00:31:32.988 --> 00:31:35.654
at least not feed, gradually weed out

842
00:31:35.654 --> 00:31:37.766
the tendencies of pettiness, selfishness,

843
00:31:37.766 --> 00:31:41.318
arrogance, sarcasm, condescension, and so forth.

844
00:31:41.318 --> 00:31:44.507
Gradually weed those out, not by just sheer muscle power,

845
00:31:44.507 --> 00:31:47.152
but by understanding and by attending closely

846
00:31:47.152 --> 00:31:49.104
to the needs of others, their yearnings,

847
00:31:49.104 --> 00:31:50.245
their hopes and fears.

848
00:31:50.245 --> 00:31:51.557
A lot of those just get washed out.

849
00:31:51.557 --> 00:31:54.117
And then attending to, like your vegetable garden,

850
00:31:54.117 --> 00:31:56.048
what are these tendencies and impulses

851
00:31:56.048 --> 00:31:59.280
in my heart and mind that are truly conducive

852
00:31:59.280 --> 00:32:01.071
to my own and others' well being,

853
00:32:01.071 --> 00:32:02.533
and cultivating those.

854
00:32:02.533 --> 00:32:04.218
So that's this whole realm

855
00:32:04.218 --> 00:32:06.394
of the cultivation of the heart and mind

856
00:32:06.394 --> 00:32:07.972
that we call meditation.

857
00:32:07.972 --> 00:32:10.234
It's not just something for religious people,

858
00:32:10.234 --> 00:32:11.716
because it's not just religious people who have

859
00:32:11.716 --> 00:32:13.135
the inner causes of suffering,

860
00:32:13.135 --> 00:32:14.297
the inner causes of happiness.

861
00:32:14.297 --> 00:32:15.673
It's really anybody.

862
00:32:15.673 --> 00:32:17.124
So, frankly, if I were asked,

863
00:32:17.124 --> 00:32:18.542
"Do you think everybody should meditate?"

864
00:32:18.542 --> 00:32:19.780
My answer would be yes.

865
00:32:19.780 --> 00:32:22.606
Now, should everybody be Buddhist?

866
00:32:22.606 --> 00:32:23.726
No.

867
00:32:23.726 --> 00:32:24.921
And this is where the preferences...

868
00:32:24.921 --> 00:32:27.384
Let's put a positive spin on preferences.

869
00:32:27.384 --> 00:32:30.126
And that is, the Dalai Lama's made this point many times,

870
00:32:30.126 --> 00:32:31.811
and I am very much a student of his,

871
00:32:31.811 --> 00:32:34.328
I agree with him entirely on this point.

872
00:32:34.328 --> 00:32:37.336
That it is not a Buddhist ideal, never has been,

873
00:32:37.336 --> 00:32:39.224
that somehow we can be clever enough,

874
00:32:39.224 --> 00:32:41.741
persuasive enough, powerful enough,

875
00:32:41.741 --> 00:32:45.111
that if we could convert everybody to Buddhism,

876
00:32:45.111 --> 00:32:47.042
now that would be really great.

877
00:32:47.042 --> 00:32:48.994
It's never been an idea in Buddhism, ever.

878
00:32:48.994 --> 00:32:50.807
Because it's not the most appropriate

879
00:32:50.807 --> 00:32:53.281
or beneficial path for everybody.

880
00:32:53.281 --> 00:32:55.724
There are some people for whom

881
00:32:55.724 --> 00:32:57.591
Christianity speaks to the heart,

882
00:32:57.591 --> 00:32:59.788
it speaks to the mind, it fills them with inspiration.

883
00:32:59.788 --> 00:33:02.262
This is absolutely where they gravitate to.

884
00:33:02.262 --> 00:33:04.353
It is their path.

885
00:33:04.353 --> 00:33:06.390
<v Interviewer>Let me ask a question at this point.</v>

886
00:33:06.390 --> 00:33:09.536
With the Tibetan faith,

887
00:33:09.536 --> 00:33:11.627
or the Tibetan practice,

888
00:33:11.627 --> 00:33:16.565
there is a belief or an understanding that this is a wheel,

889
00:33:16.565 --> 00:33:18.592
this is a wheel of life.

890
00:33:18.592 --> 00:33:20.565
To incarnate, and to incarnate again,

891
00:33:20.565 --> 00:33:23.253
and this is very much a part of the Dalai Lama's path,

892
00:33:23.253 --> 00:33:25.279
and all great Lamas.

893
00:33:25.279 --> 00:33:29.322
So might it be that a person is finding their preference,

894
00:33:29.322 --> 00:33:30.868
as you say, in a positive way,

895
00:33:30.868 --> 00:33:35.562
for a given religion as a result of this conditioning

896
00:33:35.562 --> 00:33:38.079
from other times in carrying this forward,

897
00:33:38.079 --> 00:33:40.115
out of familiarity, even?

898
00:33:40.115 --> 00:33:41.983
<v ->I think it's a very good question,</v>

899
00:33:41.983 --> 00:33:44.179
and I will speak, of course, from the Buddhist perspective,

900
00:33:44.179 --> 00:33:46.088
that's how it's couched, so.

901
00:33:46.088 --> 00:33:47.998
The answer is definitely yes.

902
00:33:47.998 --> 00:33:49.481
And I look at myself.

903
00:33:49.481 --> 00:33:52.584
I never felt really at home in the Christian world view,

904
00:33:52.584 --> 00:33:54.536
that Christ was the only son of God,

905
00:33:54.536 --> 00:33:56.648
this is the one true faith and so forth,

906
00:33:56.648 --> 00:33:58.291
and all the other religions, well,

907
00:33:58.291 --> 00:34:01.053
it kind of didn't really make it.

908
00:34:01.053 --> 00:34:02.727
Or we've heard recently just from the pope,

909
00:34:02.727 --> 00:34:05.096
saying he's kind of rather skeptical about the whole notion

910
00:34:05.096 --> 00:34:06.504
of interfaith dialogue

911
00:34:06.504 --> 00:34:08.733
as if you should somehow bracket your beliefs.

912
00:34:08.733 --> 00:34:12.477
I think he really does believe there's only one true faith,

913
00:34:12.477 --> 00:34:14.044
and so if we're going to have interfaith dialogue,

914
00:34:14.044 --> 00:34:16.114
well, would you like to know what the truth is?

915
00:34:16.114 --> 00:34:17.148
I'll tell you what the truth is.

916
00:34:17.148 --> 00:34:19.143
It's my faith, not your faith.

917
00:34:19.143 --> 00:34:22.652
He's a very intelligent man, and there are many Christians

918
00:34:22.652 --> 00:34:24.945
who are likewise, has great integrity,

919
00:34:24.945 --> 00:34:26.876
great intelligence.

920
00:34:26.876 --> 00:34:29.179
I just can't go that way,

921
00:34:29.179 --> 00:34:32.347
any more than, and this is a strong parallel,

922
00:34:32.347 --> 00:34:36.187
any more than I can think, could even imagine,

923
00:34:36.187 --> 00:34:38.480
that there's only one way to know reality,

924
00:34:38.480 --> 00:34:40.955
and that's by way of modern science and technology.

925
00:34:40.955 --> 00:34:42.831
I think, "I've heard that one before,

926
00:34:42.831 --> 00:34:44.453
"I rejected that when I was 13,

927
00:34:44.453 --> 00:34:46.384
"and I'm rejecting now at the age of 58."

928
00:34:46.384 --> 00:34:49.306
There is no one true way to truth.

929
00:34:49.306 --> 00:34:50.543
I've never believed that,

930
00:34:50.543 --> 00:34:52.677
and I just think it's provincial, closed minded thinking

931
00:34:52.677 --> 00:34:54.938
whoever does it, whether it's materialists

932
00:34:54.938 --> 00:34:58.628
or whether it's dogmatic religious people.

933
00:34:58.628 --> 00:35:03.628
So the diversity, the multiple perspectives,

934
00:35:03.791 --> 00:35:05.359
and from a religious perspective,

935
00:35:05.359 --> 00:35:06.905
I look at myself.

936
00:35:06.905 --> 00:35:08.889
Here I was a fish out of water.

937
00:35:08.889 --> 00:35:10.414
I couldn't just become a scientist.

938
00:35:10.414 --> 00:35:12.611
I thought, "That's gonna be a barren wasteland for me.

939
00:35:12.611 --> 00:35:15.011
"I'm looking for meaning and it does not deliver."

940
00:35:15.011 --> 00:35:18.744
Then I looked at religion, and that particular motif,

941
00:35:18.744 --> 00:35:20.963
it just doesn't resonate, it doesn't make any sense

942
00:35:20.963 --> 00:35:22.872
that I should follow Christianity

943
00:35:22.872 --> 00:35:24.439
because I was born in Pasadena,

944
00:35:24.439 --> 00:35:27.852
whereas if I were born in, let's say, Baghdad,

945
00:35:27.852 --> 00:35:29.026
I would be a Muslim.

946
00:35:29.026 --> 00:35:30.594
If I were born in Jerusalem I'd be...

947
00:35:30.594 --> 00:35:32.216
I'm supposed to follow something

948
00:35:32.216 --> 00:35:34.146
because of where I was born?

949
00:35:34.146 --> 00:35:35.586
And say that's the one true faith,

950
00:35:35.586 --> 00:35:36.973
because I was born in this place?

951
00:35:36.973 --> 00:35:39.628
I think, "Wait a minute.

952
00:35:39.628 --> 00:35:41.505
"I can't do that, that's ridiculous."

953
00:35:41.505 --> 00:35:44.267
I got the truth right because I was born in the right place?

954
00:35:44.267 --> 00:35:48.065
Give me a break, that just doesn't make any sense.

955
00:35:48.065 --> 00:35:51.777
So I look at myself, and there I was,

956
00:35:51.777 --> 00:35:54.646
disoriented, frustrated, disenchanted,

957
00:35:54.646 --> 00:35:56.715
not finding anything I could connect with.

958
00:35:56.715 --> 00:35:59.275
I pick up one book on Tibetan Buddhism.

959
00:35:59.275 --> 00:36:01.739
<v Interviewer>And your life does an about face.</v>

960
00:36:01.739 --> 00:36:04.331
<v ->And it was no return.</v>

961
00:36:04.331 --> 00:36:06.229
It was just no return, this is it.

962
00:36:06.229 --> 00:36:07.808
I will make any sacrifice,

963
00:36:07.808 --> 00:36:09.675
and I made large sacrifices.

964
00:36:09.675 --> 00:36:11.914
This is it, this is utterly it,

965
00:36:11.914 --> 00:36:13.258
and I will carry on through.

966
00:36:13.258 --> 00:36:15.392
I find it was very easy to learn Tibetan.

967
00:36:15.392 --> 00:36:16.565
I learned it very rapidly,

968
00:36:16.565 --> 00:36:17.685
my pronunciation's very good,

969
00:36:17.685 --> 00:36:19.413
rather like a Tibetan,

970
00:36:19.413 --> 00:36:21.812
and I've felt at home ever since.

971
00:36:21.812 --> 00:36:22.719
<v Interviewer>Interesting.</v>

972
00:36:22.719 --> 00:36:24.533
Have you any idea why you chose to incarnate

973
00:36:24.533 --> 00:36:27.273
in Pasadena, into a Christian family,

974
00:36:27.273 --> 00:36:30.441
into a Caucasian body?

975
00:36:30.441 --> 00:36:32.681
<v ->I certainly make no claims to clairvoyance,</v>

