00:36:32.681 --> 00:36:35.113
but if I should try to,

977
00:36:35.113 --> 00:36:36.115
more just in terms of...

978
00:36:36.115 --> 00:36:37.182
<v Interviewer>Your own feeling.</v>

979
00:36:37.182 --> 00:36:38.526
<v ->My own feeling, yeah,</v>

980
00:36:38.526 --> 00:36:40.617
so there makes no esoteric claims.

981
00:36:40.617 --> 00:36:44.030
I did have a sense very early on,

982
00:36:44.030 --> 00:36:46.515
that is, from the age of 20, when I encountered Buddhism,

983
00:36:46.515 --> 00:36:48.605
that I felt I'm here to be of service

984
00:36:48.605 --> 00:36:50.920
and try to bring clarity where I think there's

985
00:36:50.920 --> 00:36:52.936
a lot of muddledness.

986
00:36:52.936 --> 00:36:55.272
I've never had the motivation,

987
00:36:55.272 --> 00:36:57.885
in fact, I have rather an antipathy towards the notion

988
00:36:57.885 --> 00:37:01.181
of going out there and being an evangelist.

989
00:37:01.181 --> 00:37:02.781
You know, "Here's my way,

990
00:37:02.781 --> 00:37:04.284
"I have to get you to believe with me.

991
00:37:04.284 --> 00:37:05.788
"Come on, let's gather the flock,

992
00:37:05.788 --> 00:37:06.866
"everybody believe with me."

993
00:37:06.866 --> 00:37:08.412
I find that repugnant.

994
00:37:08.412 --> 00:37:11.526
On the other hand, as you saw me speaking this morning,

995
00:37:11.526 --> 00:37:13.169
I speak with a lot of enthusiasm.

996
00:37:13.169 --> 00:37:16.337
But it never had a notion of, "Now convert to my beliefs,"

997
00:37:16.337 --> 00:37:19.324
but the enthusiasm to dealing open mindedly,

998
00:37:19.324 --> 00:37:21.681
and empirically, and pragmatically

999
00:37:21.681 --> 00:37:23.611
with really important questions.

1000
00:37:23.611 --> 00:37:28.611
I think the type of meditations and theories that I teach

1001
00:37:28.646 --> 00:37:31.387
can be, they have been, on occasion,

1002
00:37:31.387 --> 00:37:33.487
very helpful for Christians,

1003
00:37:33.487 --> 00:37:35.194
and I've had a number of students...

1004
00:37:35.194 --> 00:37:37.104
When I was teaching at the University of California,

1005
00:37:37.104 --> 00:37:39.557
Santa Barbara, I had a number of students.

1006
00:37:39.557 --> 00:37:41.957
One young man just attended a course

1007
00:37:41.957 --> 00:37:43.482
that I took on Tibetan Buddhism.

1008
00:37:43.482 --> 00:37:45.530
He came to me afterwards and he said, "Professor Wallace,

1009
00:37:45.530 --> 00:37:47.802
"I found this course marvelous.

1010
00:37:47.802 --> 00:37:50.810
"I has really deepened my faith in Christianity."

1011
00:37:50.810 --> 00:37:52.313
He was planning to become a priest.

1012
00:37:52.313 --> 00:37:53.796
And there was no sarcasm here,

1013
00:37:53.796 --> 00:37:54.937
like, "What you taught was such hogwash,

1014
00:37:54.937 --> 00:37:56.537
"now I really believe in what I'm doing,"

1015
00:37:56.537 --> 00:37:58.190
but rather I was grappling with the issues,

1016
00:37:58.190 --> 00:37:59.993
encouraging him to do so as well,

1017
00:37:59.993 --> 00:38:02.296
and there he was, emboldened in his own faith,

1018
00:38:02.296 --> 00:38:04.121
with an appreciation of Buddhism.

1019
00:38:04.121 --> 00:38:05.561
It wasn't his path, but he said,

1020
00:38:05.561 --> 00:38:07.395
"Boy, they're really grappling with good issues,

1021
00:38:07.395 --> 00:38:09.262
"and I am too, and I'm following the Christian route."

1022
00:38:09.262 --> 00:38:11.663
Another one who was training to become a rabbit

1023
00:38:11.663 --> 00:38:13.080
told me the same thing.

1024
00:38:13.080 --> 00:38:14.242
<v Interviewer>That's marvelous,</v>

1025
00:38:14.242 --> 00:38:15.533
now you've gotten people to think.

1026
00:38:15.533 --> 00:38:16.963
<v ->That's what makes me happy.</v>

