00:40:15.067 --> 00:40:17.627
Buddhism says not, "In the beginning,

1083
00:40:17.627 --> 00:40:20.059
"God created the heavens and the Earth,"

1084
00:40:20.059 --> 00:40:21.115
but rather, "There is suffering.

1085
00:40:21.115 --> 00:40:22.480
"Take a look at it."

1086
00:40:22.480 --> 00:40:24.709
That doesn't make any allusion to God at all,

1087
00:40:24.709 --> 00:40:27.013
and it doesn't, also, make any allusion to past lives

1088
00:40:27.013 --> 00:40:28.592
or metaphysical issues.

1089
00:40:28.592 --> 00:40:31.685
There it is, so it brings us back to experience,

1090
00:40:31.685 --> 00:40:34.554
rather than taking us out of experience into some dogma.

1091
00:40:34.554 --> 00:40:36.751
And frankly, I think that's what materialism does.

1092
00:40:36.751 --> 00:40:38.415
Here we are, as you said earlier,

1093
00:40:38.415 --> 00:40:41.381
that our experience is 100% subjective.

1094
00:40:41.381 --> 00:40:43.716
100% subjective.

1095
00:40:44.936 --> 00:40:49.060
But I appear to you as a human being and so forth,

1096
00:40:49.060 --> 00:40:51.086
well, really all that's here is a brain.

1097
00:40:51.086 --> 00:40:52.997
And all this here is brain chemistry,

1098
00:40:52.997 --> 00:40:56.815
and so now I'm inviting you to come out of your experience

1099
00:40:56.815 --> 00:40:59.311
to me, as a human being with your own subjective impressions

1100
00:40:59.311 --> 00:41:00.537
and so forth,

1101
00:41:00.537 --> 00:41:01.775
and say, "Well, no, if you really want to know about me,

1102
00:41:01.775 --> 00:41:04.164
just do some brain scans and take my blood type,

1103
00:41:04.164 --> 00:41:06.116
and brain chemistry, and how much EEG..."

1104
00:41:06.116 --> 00:41:08.846
It's taking you out of experience.

1105
00:41:08.846 --> 00:41:12.036
This is what I find so ironic

1106
00:41:12.036 --> 00:41:13.763
is that this whole physical world,

1107
00:41:13.763 --> 00:41:16.355
which is the ultimate thing, the only thing

1108
00:41:16.355 --> 00:41:18.329
that's really real for the materialist

1109
00:41:18.329 --> 00:41:20.771
we've never actually seen it directly.

1110
00:41:20.771 --> 00:41:23.086
As I'm gazing over at your form here,

1111
00:41:23.086 --> 00:41:25.645
what I'm getting, of course, is visual impressions.

1112
00:41:25.645 --> 00:41:28.504
If I should touch you, I'll just touch the paper,

1113
00:41:28.504 --> 00:41:29.666
it'd be something like that,

1114
00:41:29.666 --> 00:41:31.960
I'm getting tactile impressions, right?

1115
00:41:31.960 --> 00:41:34.520
I hear your voice, I've got an auditory impression.

1116
00:41:34.520 --> 00:41:36.855
These are called qualia, these are

1117
00:41:36.855 --> 00:41:38.647
the immediate contents of experience.

1118
00:41:38.647 --> 00:41:40.173
They're not made out of matter.

1119
00:41:40.173 --> 00:41:42.199
The colours that I see are not made

1120
00:41:42.199 --> 00:41:43.543
out of molecules or atoms,

1121
00:41:43.543 --> 00:41:45.314
their not made out of fields or particles.

1122
00:41:45.314 --> 00:41:46.593
<v Interviewer>They're still perceptions.</v>

1123
00:41:46.593 --> 00:41:48.097
<v ->No, and so this whole physical world,</v>

1124
00:41:48.097 --> 00:41:50.327
that everything's supposed to boil down to the physical,

1125
00:41:50.327 --> 00:41:54.070
it is as metaphysical as somebody believing

1126
00:41:54.070 --> 00:41:55.425
everything is the will of God.

